        "username": "M00nD3v",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/m00nd3v/{size}/17595_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-06-23T23:09:39.493Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As you can see in the screenshots, the close (X) buttons in the top right corner of the popups don’t look consistent throughout the “message bubble color” and settings popup view. It would be nice if there only appears one version of a close button.<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4\" title=\"Screenshot 2021-06-24 004721\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4_2_223x375.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-06-24 004721\" data-base62-sha1=\"95Zj3iMNjMUYeehxvb8dYMiZY4A\" width=\"223\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4_2_223x375.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4_2_334x562.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/3/f/3fc0df452165412de74720a214ac4eb7949cf4c4_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2021-06-24 004721</span><span class=\"informations\">396×663 33.6 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div> <div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812\" title=\"Screenshot 2021-06-24 004626\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812_2_304x375.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-06-24 004626\" data-base62-sha1=\"kBpIFF6AINsZaRlnowITRqgdACS\" width=\"304\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812_2_304x375.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812_2_456x562.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/0/90663378f971c7a1d44b4b97b35ad291a9314812_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2021-06-24 004626</span><span class=\"informations\">549×675 27.4 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<p>I would consider “designing” the general settings-popout the way the “message bubble color”-popout looks like. Not only regarding the closing bubble but also with the font size, colors, etc.</p>\n<p>Regarding the “message bubble color”-popout, I would give the message bubbles more margin on all four sides (this would make the top and bottom margin of the horizontal divider below the message bubbles consistent again).</p>\n<p>Just an initial thought: wouldn’t it be better to make the “message-bubble-color”-popup’s content horizontal by placing the color “bubbles” on the right side of the preview instead of below? This would reduce the chance of getting an overflow within the popup.</p>",
